2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

  • Priorize year of death taken from official mortality data (the National Health Service Central Register)
  • Otherwise, keep years of death answered in EOL interviews
  • Correct an impossible year of death with the given in EOL interview
  • harmonise those id's dead during wave n (2000 + n*2,2001 + n*2) in wave n if they do not participate in it or otherwise in wave n+1

R script:

# Individuals with potential information on death and in some wave up to 0.
# Values -2,-3 of yrdeath have no useful information to harmonise
elsa <- elsa %>% filter(id %in% Reduce(union, list(core1$id, core2$id, core3$id, 
    core4$id, core5$id, core6$id, core7$id))) %>% mutate_at("yrdeath", ~replace(., 
    list = which(. %in% c(-2, -3)), values = NA)) %>% filter_at(vars(-id), any_vars(!is.na(.)))
# elsa <- elsa %>% filter(id %in%
# Reduce(union,list(core1$id,core2$id,core3$id,core4$id,core5$id,core6$id,core7$id)))
# %>% mutate_at('yrdeath',~replace(.,list = which(. %in% c(-2,-3)), values =
# NA)) %>% mutate_at('mortstat',~replace(.,list = which(. %in% c(-1,-0)),
# values = NA)) %>% filter_at(vars(-id),any_vars(!is.na(.)))

# Individuals in EoL interviews not interviewed in any wave from 1 are
# removed. We keep them only in first EoL interview they appear.  Printed
# lengths of cases 135 - 1 = 134
ids2 <- (eol2 %>% filter(id %in% Reduce(union, list(core1$id, core2$id))))$id
# 375 - 1 = 374
ids3 <- setdiff((eol3 %>% filter(id %in% Reduce(union, list(core1$id, core2$id, 
    core3$id))))$id, eol2$id)
# 242 -1 - 4 = 237
ids4 <- setdiff((eol4 %>% filter(id %in% Reduce(union, list(core1$id, core2$id, 
    core3$id, core4$id))))$id, union(eol2$id, eol3$id))
# 240
ids6 <- setdiff((eol6 %>% filter(id %in% Reduce(union, list(core1$id, core2$id, 
    core3$id, core4$id, core5$id, core6$id))))$id, Reduce(union, list(eol2$id, 
    eol3$id, eol4$id)))
# 134 + 374 + 237 + 240 = 985
ids <- Reduce(union, list(ids2, ids3, ids4, ids6))

eol <- full_join(eol2 %>% filter(id %in% ids2), eol3 %>% filter(id %in% ids3), 
    by = "id", suffix = c(".w2", ".w3"))
eol <- full_join(eol, eol4 %>% filter(id %in% ids4), by = "id")
eol <- full_join(eol, eol6 %>% filter(id %in% ids6), by = "id", suffix = c(".w4", 
    ".w6"))
eol <- eol %>% mutate(EiDateY = coalesce(EiDateY.w2, EiDateY.w3, EiDateY.w4, 
    EiDateY.w6))

# elsa_eol <- full_join(eol %>% select(id,EiDateY) %>%
# mutate_at('EiDateY',~replace(.,list = which(. %in% c(-8,2000)), values =
# NA)), elsa %>% filter(!is.na(yrdeath) | id %in% eol$id), by = 'id')

# Priorize year of death taken from official mortality data (the National
# Health Service Central Register).  Otherwise, keep years of death answered
# in EOL interviews.  Correct an impossible year of death with the given in
# EOL interview.

elsa_eol <- full_join(eol %>% select(id, EiDateY), elsa %>% filter(!is.na(yrdeath) | 
    id %in% eol$id), by = "id") %>% mutate(ydeath = coalesce(yrdeath, as.numeric(EiDateY))) %>% 
    mutate(ydeath = replace(ydeath, id %in% ids3 & yrdeath == 2010, EiDateY[which(id %in% 
        ids3 & yrdeath == 2010)]))


dids2 <- union((elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2002, 2003)))$id, (elsa_eol %>% 
    filter(ydeath %in% c(2004, 2005) & !id %in% core2$id))$id)
dids3 <- setdiff(union((elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2004, 2005)))$id, 
    (elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2006, 2007) & !id %in% core3$id))$id), 
    dids2)
dids4 <- setdiff(union((elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2006, 2007)))$id, 
    (elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2008, 2009) & !id %in% core4$id))$id), 
    dids3)
dids5 <- setdiff(union((elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2008, 2009)))$id, 
    (elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2010, 2011) & !id %in% core5$id))$id), 
    dids4)
dids6 <- setdiff(union((elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2010, 2011)))$id, 
    (elsa_eol %>% filter(ydeath %in% c(2012, 2013) & !id %in% core6$id))$id), 
    dids5)
